definition:
A man of the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.8.36; 
 son of: Jehoaddah (H3085); 
 brother of: Azmaveth (H5820H) and Zimri (H2174H)
 § Alameth or Alemeth = "covering"
1) a Benjamite, son of Jehoadah or Jerah and descended from Saul through Jonathan
2) a town in Benjamin
